  "nodes": [
    {
      "label": "vdiff-API (Breaking-Change Diff API for LLMs)",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "breaking-change-api-spec.md",
      "source_location": "\u00a71-2",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "LLMs generate code against APIs learned during training that no longer exist; existing tools report current version or current docs, but nobody serves a structured machine-readable diff between two versions as a first-class product.",
      "id": "docs_breaking_change_api_spec_vdiff_api",
      "community": 2,
      "norm_label": "vdiff-api (breaking-change diff api for llms)"
    },
    {
      "label": "MCP Server Layer",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "breaking-change-api-spec.md",
      "source_location": "\u00a75, \u00a78",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Thin protocol wrapper around the REST API; it is the distribution layer, not where logic lives, because agentic tools discover capabilities through MCP registries rather than the open web. Minimal 2-3 tool surface mirrors Context7's simplicity so agents pick it up easily.",
      "id": "docs_breaking_change_api_spec_mcp_server",
      "community": 1,
      "norm_label": "mcp server layer"
    },
    {
      "label": "REST API Layer",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "breaking-change-api-spec.md",
      "source_location": "\u00a75, \u00a77",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Stateless layer that reads from cache or triggers the diff engine; responses kept terse and machine-shaped with an explicit confidence field so agents can decide how much to trust each entry.",
      "id": "docs_breaking_change_api_spec_rest_api_layer",
      "community": 0,
      "norm_label": "rest api layer"
    },
    {
      "label": "Diff Engine",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "breaking-change-api-spec.md",
      "source_location": "\u00a75",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "On-demand compute for uncached version pairs: first request slow (seconds), result stored so subsequent identical requests are instant. The signature-diffing engine is the actual IP, not aggregation.",
      "id": "docs_breaking_change_api_spec_diff_engine",
      "community": 0,
      "norm_label": "diff engine"
    },
    {
      "label": "Postgres Cache Database",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "breaking-change-api-spec.md",
      "source_location": "\u00a76",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Non-optional: diffs are expensive to compute (package download, AST/type parsing), so results must be cached; also tracks diffed (package, version_a, version_b) triples and a queue/status table so concurrent identical requests don't duplicate work. JSONB chosen for breaking-changes payload because the shape varies too much for a rigid relational model, while diff_requests_log stays relational for billing/analytics.",
      "id": "docs_breaking_change_api_spec_postgres_cache",
      "community": 0,
      "norm_label": "postgres cache database"
    },
    {
      "label": "Ingestion Workers",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "breaking-change-api-spec.md",
      "source_location": "\u00a75, \u00a79",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Scheduled (not real-time) background jobs that watch popular-package releases and pre-compute diffs so common queries are cache hits; simple cron is enough for v1, real queue only when volume demands it. Must use respectful backoff against npm/PyPI/GitHub rate limits.",
      "id": "docs_breaking_change_api_spec_ingestion_workers",
      "community": 0,
      "norm_label": "ingestion workers"
    },
    {
      "label": "Structural Diffing (Tier 2)",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "breaking-change-api-spec.md",
      "source_location": "\u00a74",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Key design decision: structural diffing is ground truth and cheap to trust, and must remain the primary source; it gives type-level signature changes but cannot catch pure runtime behavior changes, a limitation the API must surface via the confidence field rather than overclaim.",
      "id": "docs_breaking_change_api_spec_structural_diffing",
      "community": 3,
      "norm_label": "structural diffing (tier 2)"
    },
    {
      "label": "Changelog LLM Extraction (Tier 3)",
      "file_type": "rationale",
      "source_file": "breaking-change-api-spec.md",
      "source_location": "\u00a74",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Prose changelogs are noisy and inconsistent, so LLM-extracted breaking-change bullets are a supplement flagged with lower confidence, never the primary source \u2014 letting LLM extraction silently become the data would reintroduce the hallucination problem the product exists to solve.",
      "id": "docs_breaking_change_api_spec_changelog_llm_extraction",
      "community": 0,
      "norm_label": "changelog llm extraction (tier 3)"
    },
    {
      "label": ".d.ts Type Declaration Diffing",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "breaking-change-api-spec.md",
      "source_location": "\u00a74, \u00a712",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "For TS/JS packages shipping .d.ts files, diffing type declarations between versions is the single highest-value, most tractable source of signature-changed facts because it is structured data, not prose; chosen as the sole diffing method for the Phase 1 MVP.",
      "id": "docs_breaking_change_api_spec_dts_diffing",
      "community": 3,
      "norm_label": ".d.ts type declaration diffing"
    },
    {
      "label": "Python AST Signature Diffing",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "breaking-change-api-spec.md",
      "source_location": "\u00a74, \u00a712",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Parse package source (downloaded via pip download into a sandbox) with the stdlib ast module to extract public function/class signatures per version, then diff; no heavier tooling needed in v1. Deferred to Phase 2.",
      "id": "docs_breaking_change_api_spec_python_ast_diffing",
      "community": 3,
      "norm_label": "python ast signature diffing"
    },
    {
      "label": "/v1/diff Endpoint",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "breaking-change-api-spec.md",
      "source_location": "\u00a77, \u00a716",
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Pairwise version diff is the core primitive because it is cheap, cacheable, and high-confidence, and maps onto the dominant real trigger: a dependency bump where the only question is what changed between the pinned version and the target.",
      "id": "docs_breaking_change_api_spec_diff_endpoint",
      "community": 4,
      "norm_label": "/v1/diff endpoint"
    },
    {
      "label": "/v1/resolve Endpoint",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "breaking-change-api-spec.md",
